<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="620" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                            <head>No. 618.<lb/><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-16"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 16,
                                        1873</date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Mr. Layard informs me he has received instructions from his
                                government concerning seventeen British subjects among the crew of
                                the Vir-ginius executed, and seven more under sentence of death, the
                                latter all minors. Of the seventeen dead, six were executed
                                immediately on the arrival of the Virginius in port. A British
                                frigate is ordered to Santiago.</p>
                            <closer><signed>SICKLES.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>